  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - SHAMAN</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>ICE GIANT MASSACRE: SOLO-TACTICS FOR THE 50 SHAMAN</font> - <small>Stormwielder Dragonheart, Povar</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>
 Soloing at 50 (this example will use an ice giant as the example, but this is the strategy to use vs. all high level mobs while soloing.)
<p> A. Spells to have loaded (you have 8 slots and 50 spells..what to do, what to do.)
<p> 1. First slot : Greater Heal (throughout the game from 29 to 50, you should always have this loaded in the same slot for quick healing.)
<p> 2. Second slot : Root (forget enstill; it is worthless. Stick with root, and ALWAYS have it hotkeyed. I use hotkey 3 for this, keeping it directly next to my nuke at hotkey 4)

<p> 3. Third slot : This is my utility slot. First, put your spell Frenzied Spirit here and make your pet, then unload it and replace it with Alacrity. 
<p> 4. fourth slot : Blizzard Blast. I always keep my highest level direct damage here and have it hotkeyed to slot 4 as well. We wont use it in this example of soloing and permafrost isnt exactly the place to use ice based nuke spells since the mobs have higher cold resist than most.
<p> 5. Fifth slot : Togor's insects. The most effective Debuff vs. any hard hitting mob. (It reduces attack speed substantially and is perfect for any high level mob whether soloing or grouping.)
<p> 6. Sixth slot : Envenomed Bolt. The highest level poison spell. Does approx 1200 dmg in 39 seconds. Set to hotkey 5.
<p> 7. Seventh slot : Plague. The highest level disease spell. Does approx 1200 dmg in 2 minutes.Set to hotkey 6. Poison and disease spells stack, meaning their effects run concurrently.
<p> 8. Spirit of Wolf : Yeah, I always have this loaded.

<p>
<p>
 Setting up
<p>   1. Buffs are optional. They make a big difference; however, when soloing, a shaman can roughly overpower anything 45 and below with only his spells, so this melee option is just that... an option. 
<p>   2. Im going to assume that you dont have the Blight Hammer in this example, and tell you how to do it with spells and pet. If you have a hammer, feel free to whack away.
<p>   3. ALWAYS ALWAYS ALWAYS cast Alacrity (substantial increase in attack speed) on your pet RIGHT before you engage the enemy.! If youre pet is fighting without alacrity, youre doing something wrong.

<p><p>
 The Battle Ensues
<p>
1. Lure the beast with Togor's Insects. (Aye, he's not rooted, so he will start after you. This is good, though, because your pet jumps immediately into action. Who really likes typing : /pet kill? )
<p>
2. Cast root (hotkey 3) This wont be a problem, togor's wont be resisted much at level 50 and your dog taunts like a bad boy. When he's rooted, back off. 
<p> 3. Cast Plague (hotkey 6) 
<p> 4. Cast Envenomed Bolt (hotkey 5)
<p> 5. In 40 seconds, cast Envenomed Bolt again (hotkey 5.)
<p> 6. Watch your pet's health as he and your DoT spells beat down the enemy, heal him if necessary. If the mob turns to you, either take a beating for a few minutes or root again. Dont let your pet die; that's a waste of mana. I never understood why people kill pets just to try again for a higher level one, or refuse to heal a pet. Be efficient with your mana; take care of your pet.
<p>
<p> The Aftermath
<p> Cast chloroplast on yourself if you get beat up. Your pet regens fast enough, but use /pet sit down if you want him to regen faster.
<p> Med to full. Repeat until the bloodthirst has been sufficiently quenched.

</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
